-- Russian Equity Movers: Aeroflot, E.On, Magnitogorsk, Raspadskaya
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-07-03T15:49:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/russian-equity-movers-aeroflot-e-on-magnitogorsk-raspadskaya.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 2.5
percent to 1,437.45 by the close in Moscow, the highest level
since May 3.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX) gained 2.3 percent to 44.48 rubles,
the highest level since June 19. The state-controlled airline
had its longest streak of gains in a month after Vedomosti
reported its biggest unit may join its parent servicing the
route between Moscow and Nice,  France .  E.On  Russia  (EONR RX) rallied 1.2 percent to 2.5106 rubles,
the highest level since June 18. The power company raised its
profit forecast after reaching a long-term price agreement with
OAO Gazprom, Russia’s natural gas export monopoly. Gazprom (GAZP
RX) gained 2.4 percent to 159 rubles, the strongest since May
10.  OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel (MAGN RX) gained 4.9 percent
to 9.926 rubles, the strongest since May 22. The Russian
steelmaker climbed after dropping a proposed takeover of
 Australia ’s Flinders Mines Ltd. yesterday.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX) rose 8 percent to 80.56 rubles,
the most since Feb. 13. Troika Dialog raised its recommendation
for the Russian coal producer to buy from hold, citing strong
 cash flow , low valuations and dividend potential.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
